$ Oracle Active Session History (ASH)
@ Active Session History

Each second, the performance relevant figures for each active → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/session are stored in memory.
-
The figures can be queried from `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/active/session_history`.

ASH can be used for diagnosing → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/performance-tuning[performance] problems.

ASH is an integral part of the *database self-management framework*.

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/dynamic-performance-views/ash_info` shows some information about the Active Session History sampling process.

  → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/rdbms/admin/ashrpt_sql[`$ORACLE_HOME/admin/rdbms/ashrpt.sql`] is an → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus script to generate an ASH report.

  → development/databases/Oracle/tools/oradebug/dump/ashdump[`oradebug dump ashdump`]
